    <name>JellyPie</name>
    <summary>Minimalist Single-File Text Editor with Todo List Features</summary>

    <description>
        <p>
            JellyPie is a minimalist single-file text editor designed for simplicity and todo list management.
        </p>
        <p>
            Built on GTK4 with a streamlined interface, JellyPie focuses on editing one file at a time with special features for task tracking.
        </p>
        <p>Key features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Single-file focus for distraction-free editing</li>
            <li>Built-in todo list support with Ctrl+D to mark tasks as done</li>
            <li>Inline text formatting: **bold**, *italic*, `monospace`</li>
            <li>Syntax highlighting with customizable color schemes</li>
            <li>Automatic file change detection and window state persistence</li>
            <li>Config-based customization of fonts, shortcuts, and behavior</li>
        </ul>
    </description>

    <launchable type="desktop-id">com.github.jdalbey.jellypie.desktop</launchable>

    <url type="homepage">https://github.com/jdalbey/jellypie-todo</url>
